 King Williams Town - A  King Williams Town man is expected in court on Tuesday after he was arrested by local police for possession of an illegal firearm. "On Sunday, at about 12:30, members of the King Williams Town K9 Unit and Flying Squad followed up information about a vehicle that was said to have an unlicensed firearm," said police spokesperson, Captain Siphokazi Mawisa. "They spotted a white Isuzu bakkie in town and chased it until it stopped at Ngxwalane location. "The vehicle was searched and a magazine with 15 9mm rounds was recovered in the cabin hole." She said that while chasing the car, police saw something being thrown out of the motor vehicle and an explosives dog named Chikka was used to search the open area. "The dog reacted positive and a 9mm victor pistol with serial no.filed off was recoverd. The suspect was immediately arrested for possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition." Capt Mawisa said that he will appear at the Zwelitsha Magistrate's Court on Tuesday. King Williams Town SAPS Cluster Commander, Brigadier Luntu, thanked the community for sharing valuable information that led to the arrest of the suspect. "Police will quickly act on information received and ensure that perpetrators are behind bars," he added. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 